@startuml ArchitectureOverview
title Architecture Overview

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontSize 13
skinparam classFontStyle Bold
skinparam classAttributeFontSize 12

package "UI Layer" <<Layer>> #EDE7F6 {
    class GUIRenderer <<UI>> {
        + {abstract} render()
    }
}

package "Game Logic Layer" <<Layer>> #E8F5E9 {

    class GameEngine <<Domain>> {
        + initNewGame()
        + processPlayerTurn()
        + checkWinCondition()
    }

    class BoardAndTiles <<Domain>> {
        + getTile()
        + getNextIndex()
        + validate()
    }

    class Property <<Domain>> {
        + getAssetValue()
        + calculateRent()
        + activateFestival()
    }

    class Player <<Domain>> {
        + getBalance()
        + getHandCards()
        + getStatus()
    }

    class CardAndDeck <<Domain>> {
        + draw()
        + shuffle()
        + execute()
    }
}

package "Data Layer" <<Layer>> #FFF8E1 {
    class DataLayer <<Domain>> {
        + loadGameConfig()
        + saveGame()
        + loadGame()
        + getFullLog()
    }
}

note bottom of GameEngine
  <b>«cross-cutting concern»</b>
  Exception / Error Handling
  (GameException hierarchy)
  dapat dilempar dan ditangkap
  di semua domain
end note

GameEngine *-down- BoardAndTiles  : owns
GameEngine *-down- Property       : owns
GameEngine *-down- Player         : owns
GameEngine *-down- CardAndDeck    : owns

BoardAndTiles -right-> Property   : PropertyTile\nrefs Property*

Player *-right- CardAndDeck       : owns Hand\n(SkillCard)

GUIRenderer ..down..> GameEngine  : reads state

DataLayer ..up..> GameEngine      : builds &\nserializes

Player "0..1" -left- "0..*" Property  : owns Property\n(Property)

@enduml